<p>Why the <code>[0]</code> part? It won't be too common, but one field could have multiple errors,
like a username that contains invalid characters <em>and</em> is too short. So each field
will have an array of errors, and we're checking that the first is set to our clever
message.</p>
<p>And since we <em>are</em> sending a valid <code>avatarNumber</code>, let's make sure that there is
<em>no</em> error for it. Use <code>assertResponsePropertyDoesNotExist()</code> and pass it <code>errors.avatarNumber</code>:</p>
